HEADWORD: Muchness
<hw>Much"ness</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Greatness; extent.</def>
<mark>[Obs. or Colloq.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The quantity and <qex>muchness</qex> of time which it
filcheth.</q> <rj><qau>W. Whately.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Much of a muchness</b></col>, <cd>much the same.</cd>
<mark>[Colloq.]</mark> ⟦ldquo⟧Men's men; gentle or simple, they're
<xex>much of a muchness</xex>.⟦rdquo⟧ <rj><au>G.
Eliot.</au></rj></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

